# Developer Portfolio – React, Node.js, PostgreSQL

This is my **personal developer portfolio** showcasing my skills, projects, and experience, built as a full-stack application with React on the frontend and Node.js + PostgreSQL on the backend, containerized with Docker and deployed with Netlify/GitHub Pages. [github](https://github.com/SaiVinay023/Portfolio_website_using_React)

***

## Live Demo

- **Portfolio URL**: https://svmanda.netlify.app/ [github](https://github.com/SaiVinay023/Portfolio_website_using_React)

***

## Features Implemented

### Frontend (React)

- **Multi-page navigation with React Router**
  - Routing between sections like About, Projects, Contact, etc. using `react-router-dom`. [github](https://github.com/SaiVinay023/Portfolio_website_using_React)
  - Menu bar navigation wired to routes for smooth SPA-like transitions. [github](https://github.com/SaiVinay023/Portfolio_website_using_React)
- **Responsive navigation bar**
  - Top menu with route-based navigation and active link highlighting. [github](https://github.com/SaiVinay023/Portfolio_website_using_React)
- **Reusable UI components**
  - Button components styled with Tailwind CSS, customizable via props (e.g., GitHub, demo, resume links). [github](https://github.com/SaiVinay023/Portfolio_website_using_React)
  - Card components for projects with hover effects, tech stack, description, and external links. [github](https://github.com/SaiVinay023/Portfolio_website_using_React)
- **Modern styling**
  - Tailwind CSS for utility-first styling. [github](https://github.com/SaiVinay023/Portfolio_website_using_React)
  - Animations and micro-interactions using Framer Motion. [github](https://github.com/SaiVinay023/Portfolio_website_using_React)
- **Projects section**
  - Dynamic list of projects with title, tech stack, description, and links (e.g., GitHub repo like `ai-chatbot`). [github](https://github.com/SaiVinay023/Portfolio_website_using_React)
- **Responsive design**
  - Optimized layout for desktop, tablet, and mobile devices. [github](https://github.com/SaiVinay023/Portfolio_website_using_React)

### Backend & Infrastructure

> The repo is structured for a **full-stack setup** with `frontend/` and `backend/` plus Docker support. [github](https://github.com/SaiVinay023/Portfolio_website_using_React)

- **Backend (Node.js + REST APIs)**
  - `backend/` folder for Node.js backend that can expose REST APIs (e.g., contact form, dynamic data). [github](https://github.com/SaiVinay023/Portfolio_website_using_React)
  - PostgreSQL used as the primary database, configured via Docker and `docker-compose.yml`. [github](https://github.com/SaiVinay023/Portfolio_website_using_React)
- **Dockerized environment**
  - `docker-compose.yml` to orchestrate app and PostgreSQL containers. [github](https://github.com/SaiVinay023/Portfolio_website_using_React)
- **Tooling & quality**
  - Development with VS Code, Prettier, ESLint, and Postman for API testing. [github](https://github.com/SaiVinay023/Portfolio_website_using_React)

### Deployment

- **Netlify / GitHub Pages deployment**
  - Auto-deploy pipeline from GitHub to Netlify / GitHub Pages. [github](https://github.com/SaiVinay023/Portfolio_website_using_React)
  - Build command: `npm run build`. [github](https://github.com/SaiVinay023/Portfolio_website_using_React)
  - Publish directory: `dist/` (Vite build output). [github](https://github.com/SaiVinay023/Portfolio_website_using_React)
  - Commit to `main` triggers a new deployment. [github](https://github.com/SaiVinay023/Portfolio_website_using_React)

***

## Tech Stack

- **Frontend**: React.js, Vite, Tailwind CSS, Framer Motion. [github](https://github.com/SaiVinay023/Portfolio_website_using_React)
- **Routing**: `react-router-dom`. [github](https://github.com/SaiVinay023/Portfolio_website_using_React)
- **Backend**: Node.js (REST APIs planned/used via `backend/`). [github](https://github.com/SaiVinay023/Portfolio_website_using_React)
- **Database**: PostgreSQL (via Docker Compose). [github](https://github.com/SaiVinay023/Portfolio_website_using_React)
- **Tooling**: VS Code, Prettier, ESLint, Postman. [github](https://github.com/SaiVinay023/Portfolio_website_using_React)
- **Deployment**: Netlify, GitHub Pages. [github](https://github.com/SaiVinay023/Portfolio_website_using_React)
- **Containerization**: Docker, `docker-compose.yml`. [github](https://github.com/SaiVinay023/Portfolio_website_using_React)

***

## Project Structure

```bash
Portfolio_website_using_React/
├── backend/              # Node.js backend (APIs, DB integration)
├── frontend/             # React frontend source code
├── docker-compose.yml    # Docker setup for app + PostgreSQL
├── .gitignore            # Git ignore rules
└── Readme                # Project documentation (this file)
```


> Inside `frontend/`, the app is structured as a typical React project with pages, components (buttons, cards, navbar), and routing configuration. [github](https://github.com/SaiVinay023/Portfolio_website_using_React)
> `backend/` is reserved for API and database logic (Node.js + PostgreSQL), wired through Docker. [github](https://github.com/SaiVinay023/Portfolio_website_using_React)

***

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Node.js (LTS)
- npm or yarn
- Docker & Docker Compose (for backend + DB, if you run full stack) [github](https://github.com/SaiVinay023/Portfolio_website_using_React)

### Clone the repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/SaiVinay023/Portfolio_website_using_React.git
cd Portfolio_website_using_React
```


### Run the frontend locally

```bash
cd frontend
npm install
npm run dev
```

Then open `http://localhost:5173` in your browser (Vite default). [github](https://github.com/SaiVinay023/Portfolio_website_using_React)

### (Optional) Run backend + PostgreSQL with Docker

```bash
docker-compose up -d
```

This spins up the backend and Postgres containers as configured in `docker-compose.yml`. [github](https://github.com/SaiVinay023/Portfolio_website_using_React)

***

## Deployment (Netlify)

1. Push this repository to GitHub. [github](https://github.com/SaiVinay023/Portfolio_website_using_React)
2. Create a new site in Netlify and connect it to this repo. [github](https://github.com/SaiVinay023/Portfolio_website_using_React)
3. Set:
   - **Build command**: `npm run build`
   - **Publish directory**: `dist/` [github](https://github.com/SaiVinay023/Portfolio_website_using_React)
4. Every push to `main` auto-triggers a new deployment. [github](https://github.com/SaiVinay023/Portfolio_website_using_React)

